This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically in the context of language models and bias. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a regularization loss term for the language model, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses social biases, which could fall under the category of cybernetics or sociology, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method, which could fall under the category of social and information sciences, making cs.SI (Social and Information Sciences) another possible sub-category.
